        <headline>Flash Flood Warning issued June 6 at 3:28PM EDT until June 6 at 6:30PM EDT by NWS Albany NY</headline>
        <description>FFWALY

The National Weather Service in Albany has issued a

* Flash Flood Warning for...
Western Albany County in east central New York...
East Central Schoharie County in east central New York...

* Until 630 PM EDT.

* At 328 PM EDT, Doppler radar indicated thunderstorms producing
heavy rain across the warned area. Between 1 and 2 inches of rain
have fallen. Additional rainfall amounts up to 1 inch are possible
in the warned area. Flash flooding is ongoing or expected to begin
shortly.

HAZARD...Flash flooding caused by thunderstorms.

SOURCE...Radar.

IMPACT...Flash flooding of small creeks and streams, urban
areas, highways, streets and underpasses as well as
other poor drainage and low-lying areas.

* Some locations that will experience flash flooding include...
Westerlo, Berne, Voorheesville, Altamont, Livingstonville, New
Scotland, Knox, Rensselaerville, Clarksville, East Berne, Bensons
Corners, Helderberg, Thompsons Lake, South Berne, Wolf Hill,
Bramans Corners, Thatcher State Park, Reidsville, Snyders Corners
and East Township.
</description>
        <instruction>Turn around, don't drown when encountering flooded roads. Most flood
deaths occur in vehicles.</instruction>
